<paragraph blockId="157.[128,654,621,1319]" pageId="157" pageNumber="157">
DISCUSSION: 
<taxonomicName authority="Menard" authorityName="Menard" authorityYear="2010" box="[337,579,622,645]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Schuhistes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[337,456,622,645]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="157">Schuhistes</emphasis>
Menard
</taxonomicName>
was placed in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh" authorityYear="1974" box="[307,526,652,674]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Leucophoropterini">Leucophoropterini</taxonomicName>
based on its superficial similarity to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh" authorityYear="1974" box="[453,598,682,703]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Karoocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[453,598,682,703]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="157">Karoocapsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its relatively small, simple endosoma and genital capsule. However, unlike all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Leucophoropterini">Leucophoropterini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menard" authorityYear="2010" box="[294,413,769,792]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Schuhistes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,413,769,792]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="157">Schuhistes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has relatively large pulvilli that nearly encompass the length of the underside of the claw (
<bibRefCitation author="Menard, K. L." box="[475,651,828,850]" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" pagination="49 - 57" refId="ref114396" refString="Menard, K. L. 2010. Description of Schuhistes n. gen. (Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae), a new plant bug genus found on endemic Lycium spp. (Solanaceae) from South Africa. Entomologica Americana 116 (1 / 2): 49 - 57." type="journal article" year="2010">Menard, 2010</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3b), and brachypterous, rounded wings in females that barely cover the apex of the abdomen (
<bibRefCitation author="Menard, K. L." box="[252,421,916,938]" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" pagination="49 - 57" refId="ref114396" refString="Menard, K. L. 2010. Description of Schuhistes n. gen. (Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae), a new plant bug genus found on endemic Lycium spp. (Solanaceae) from South Africa. Entomologica Americana 116 (1 / 2): 49 - 57." type="journal article" year="2010">Menard, 2010</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Leucophoropterini">Leucophoropterini</taxonomicName>
have pulvilli that only partially cover the ventral surface of the claw, and females have complete wings that extend past the apex of the abdomen. With the pending removal of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh" authorityYear="1974" box="[259,404,1063,1084]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Karoocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[259,404,1063,1084]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="157">Karoocapsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Leucophoropterini">Leucophoropterini</taxonomicName>
, as well as it grouping with several other South African taxa in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Douglas &amp; Scott" authorityYear="1865" box="[521,603,1121,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phylini">Phylini</taxonomicName>
not closely related to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuh" authorityYear="1974" box="[392,611,1151,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Leucophoropterini">Leucophoropterini</taxonomicName>
on the basis of morphological and molecular data (Menard et al., in press), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menard" authorityYear="2010" box="[505,624,1209,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Schuhistes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[505,624,1209,1232]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="157">Schuhistes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is temporarily placed in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Douglas &amp; Scott" authorityYear="1865" box="[462,544,1239,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phylini">Phylini</taxonomicName>
pending placement with other South African taxa in a new tribe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
